2301 - <div class="floatleft"><a href="http://vignette2.wikia.nocookie.net/runescape2/images/4/42/Pineapple_pizza_detail.png/revision/latest?cb=20140316000853" 	class="image image-thumbnail" 	 	 	><img src="data:image/gif;base64R0lGODlhAQABAIABAAAAAP///yH5BAEAAAEALAAAAAABAAEAQAICTAEAOw%3D%3D" 	 alt="Pineapple pizza detail" 	class="lzy lzyPlcHld " 	 	data-image-key="Pineapple_pizza_detail.png" 	data-image-name="Pineapple pizza detail.png" 	 data-src="http://vignette2.wikia.nocookie.net/runescape2/images/4/42/Pineapple_pizza_detail.png/revision/latest/scale-to-width-down/100?cb=20140316000853" 	 width="100" 	 height="91" 	 	 	 onload="if(typeof ImgLzy=== #39;object #39;){ImgLzy.load(this)}" 	><noscript><img src="http://vignette2.wikia.nocookie.net/runescape2/images/4/42/Pineapple_pizza_detail.png/revision/latest/scale-to-width-down/100?cb=20140316000853" 	 alt="Pineapple pizza detail" 	class="" 	 	data-image-key="Pineapple_pizza_detail.png" 	data-image-name="Pineapple pizza detail.png" 	 	 width="100" 	 height="91" 	 	 	 	></noscript></a></div><b>Pineapple pizza</b> is the highest level pizza in <i>RuneScape</i> healing 1624 <a href="/wiki/Life_Points" title="Life Points" class="mw-redirect">Life Points</a> (812 per bite). It can be made at level 65 <a href="/wiki/Cooking" title="Cooking">Cooking</a> by adding <a href="/wiki/Pineapple_chunks" title="Pineapple chunks">pineapple chunks</a> or <a href="/wiki/Pineapple_ring" title="Pineapple ring">pineapple rings</a> to a cooked <a href="/wiki/Plain_pizza" title="Plain pizza">plain pizza</a> and gives 197 total experience (52 experience for adding the <a href="/wiki/Pineapple" title="Pineapple">pineapple</a> to the plain pizza).

3408 - <p><b>Serum 207</b> is a temporary cure for the <a href="/wiki/Afflicted" title="Afflicted">afflicted</a> villagers of <a href="/wiki/Mort%27ton" title="Mort'ton">Mort'ton</a> who are otherwise incoherent. A player who has read the <a href="/wiki/Diary_of_Herbi_Flax" title="Diary of Herbi Flax" class="mw-redirect">Diary of Herbi Flax</a> during the quest <a href="/wiki/Shades_of_Mort%27ton" title="Shades of Mort'ton">Shades of Mort'ton</a> and has a <a href="/wiki/Herblore" title="Herblore">Herblore</a> level of at least 15 may produce it by adding <a href="/wiki/Clean_tarromin" title="Clean tarromin">Clean tarromin</a> to a <a href="/wiki/Vial_of_water" title="Vial of water">vial of water</a> and then adding <a href="/wiki/Ashes" title="Ashes">Ashes</a> giving 50 herblore <a href="/wiki/Experience" title="Experience">experience</a>.

3415 - 1 coin
3416 - <p><b>Serum 208</b> is a permanent cure for the <a href="/wiki/Afflicted" title="Afflicted">afflicted</a> villagers of <a href="/wiki/Mort%27ton" title="Mort'ton">Mort'ton</a>. It is used during the <a href="/wiki/Shades_of_Mort%27ton" title="Shades of Mort'ton">Shades of Mort'ton</a> quest to turn Afflicted NPCs back into normal characters so the player can interact with them. It is made by using <a href="/wiki/Serum_207" title="Serum 207">Serum 207</a> on the sacred flame at the rebuilt temple.
3417 - <p><b>Serum 208</b> is a permanent cure for the <a href="/wiki/Afflicted" title="Afflicted">afflicted</a> villagers of <a href="/wiki/Mort%27ton" title="Mort'ton">Mort'ton</a>. It is used during the <a href="/wiki/Shades_of_Mort%27ton" title="Shades of Mort'ton">Shades of Mort'ton</a> quest to turn Afflicted NPCs back into normal characters so the player can interact with them. It is made by using <a href="/wiki/Serum_207" title="Serum 207">Serum 207</a> on the sacred flame at the rebuilt temple.
3418 - <p><b>Serum 208</b> is a permanent cure for the <a href="/wiki/Afflicted" title="Afflicted">afflicted</a> villagers of <a href="/wiki/Mort%27ton" title="Mort'ton">Mort'ton</a>. It is used during the <a href="/wiki/Shades_of_Mort%27ton" title="Shades of Mort'ton">Shades of Mort'ton</a> quest to turn Afflicted NPCs back into normal characters so the player can interact with them. It is made by using <a href="/wiki/Serum_207" title="Serum 207">Serum 207</a> on the sacred flame at the rebuilt temple.
3419 - <p><b>Serum 208</b> is a permanent cure for the <a href="/wiki/Afflicted" title="Afflicted">afflicted</a> villagers of <a href="/wiki/Mort%27ton" title="Mort'ton">Mort'ton</a>. It is used during the <a href="/wiki/Shades_of_Mort%27ton" title="Shades of Mort'ton">Shades of Mort'ton</a> quest to turn Afflicted NPCs back into normal characters so the player can interact with them. It is made by using <a href="/wiki/Serum_207" title="Serum 207">Serum 207</a> on the sacred flame at the rebuilt temple.

4726 - <p><b>Guthan's warspear</b> is a <a href="/wiki/Weapons#Member_melee_weapons" title="Weapons" class="mw-redirect">melee weapon</a> that is part of <a href="/wiki/Guthan_the_Infested%27s_equipment" title="Guthan the Infested's equipment">Guthan The Infested's set</a> of <a href="/wiki/Barrows_equipment" title="Barrows equipment">barrows equipment</a>. Guthan's warspear is a two handed weapon and requires 70 <a href="/wiki/Attack" title="Attack">Attack</a> to wield. This weapon <b>cannot</b> be made using the <a href="/wiki/Smithing" title="Smithing">Smithing</a> <a href="/wiki/Skill" title="Skill" class="mw-redirect">skill</a>.

4728 - <p><b>Guthan's platebody</b> is <a href="/wiki/Armour#Melee_armour" title="Armour">melee armour</a> worn in the <a href="/wiki/Inventory#Body_Slot" title="Inventory">body slot</a> that is part of <a href="/wiki/Guthan_the_Infested%27s_equipment" title="Guthan the Infested's equipment">Guthan The Infested's set</a> of <a href="/wiki/Barrows_equipment" title="Barrows equipment">barrows equipment</a>. To wear Guthan's platebody a player must have 70 <a href="/wiki/Defence" title="Defence">Defence</a>. It is currently tied with <a href="/wiki/Torag%27s_platebody" title="Torag's platebody">Torag's platebody</a> and <a href="/wiki/Dharok%27s_platebody" title="Dharok's platebody">Dharok's platebody</a> as being the third strongest platebody in the game behind <a href="/wiki/Statius%27s_platebody" title="Statius's platebody">Statius's platebody</a> and the <a href="/wiki/Torva_platebody" title="Torva platebody">Torva platebody</a>.

4734 - <p><b>Karil's crossbow</b> is a <a href="/wiki/Two-handed_crossbow" title="Two-handed crossbow">Two-handed crossbow</a> <a href="/wiki/Weapons#Member_ranged_weapons" title="Weapons" class="mw-redirect">ranged weapon</a> that is part of <a href="/wiki/Karil_the_Tainted%27s_equipment" title="Karil the Tainted's equipment">Karil the Tainted's set</a> of <a href="/wiki/Barrows_equipment" title="Barrows equipment">barrows equipment</a>. To wield the crossbow players require a <a href="/wiki/Ranged" title="Ranged">Ranged</a> level of 70. It requires ammunition called <a href="/wiki/Bolt_rack" title="Bolt rack">bolt racks</a>. Both the Karil's crossbow and Karil's pistol crossbow are the only crossbows to use bolt racks.

4747 - <p><b>Torag's hammer</b> is a 2-handed <a href="/wiki/Weapons#Member_two-handed_melee_weapons" title="Weapons" class="mw-redirect">melee weapon</a> that is part of <a href="/wiki/Torag_the_Corrupted%27s_equipment" title="Torag the Corrupted's equipment">Torag the Corrupted's set</a> of <a href="/wiki/Barrows_equipment" title="Barrows equipment">barrows equipment</a>. To wield Torag's hammer a player must have 70 <a href="/wiki/Attack" title="Attack">Attack</a> and <a href="/wiki/Strength" title="Strength">Strength</a>.
4748 - 0 coins
4749 - <p><b>Torag's platebody</b> is <a href="/wiki/Armour#Melee_armour" title="Armour">melee armour</a> worn in the <a href="/wiki/Inventory#body_Slot" title="Inventory">body slot</a> that is part of <a href="/wiki/Torag_the_Corrupted%27s_equipment" title="Torag the Corrupted's equipment">Torag The Corrupted's set</a> of <a href="/wiki/Barrows_equipment" title="Barrows equipment">barrows equipment</a>. To wear Torag's platebody a player must have 70 <a href="/wiki/Defence" title="Defence">Defence</a>. Torag's platebody is also one of the strongest platebodies in RuneScape but it has the downside of degrading after 10 hours. When clicking "check" on the platebody it will show you its charges left. When it has fully degraded it turns to a broken torag's platebody.

4914 - <p><b>Guthan's warspear</b> is a <a href="/wiki/Weapons#Member_melee_weapons" title="Weapons" class="mw-redirect">melee weapon</a> that is part of <a href="/wiki/Guthan_the_Infested%27s_equipment" title="Guthan the Infested's equipment">Guthan The Infested's set</a> of <a href="/wiki/Barrows_equipment" title="Barrows equipment">barrows equipment</a>. Guthan's warspear is a two handed weapon and requires 70 <a href="/wiki/Attack" title="Attack">Attack</a> to wield. This weapon <b>cannot</b> be made using the <a href="/wiki/Smithing" title="Smithing">Smithing</a> <a href="/wiki/Skill" title="Skill" class="mw-redirect">skill</a>.

4920 - <p><b>Guthan's platebody</b> is <a href="/wiki/Armour#Melee_armour" title="Armour">melee armour</a> worn in the <a href="/wiki/Inventory#Body_Slot" title="Inventory">body slot</a> that is part of <a href="/wiki/Guthan_the_Infested%27s_equipment" title="Guthan the Infested's equipment">Guthan The Infested's set</a> of <a href="/wiki/Barrows_equipment" title="Barrows equipment">barrows equipment</a>. To wear Guthan's platebody a player must have 70 <a href="/wiki/Defence" title="Defence">Defence</a>. It is currently tied with <a href="/wiki/Torag%27s_platebody" title="Torag's platebody">Torag's platebody</a> and <a href="/wiki/Dharok%27s_platebody" title="Dharok's platebody">Dharok's platebody</a> as being the third strongest platebody in the game behind <a href="/wiki/Statius%27s_platebody" title="Statius's platebody">Statius's platebody</a> and the <a href="/wiki/Torva_platebody" title="Torva platebody">Torva platebody</a>.

4938 - <p><b>Karil's crossbow</b> is a <a href="/wiki/Two-handed_crossbow" title="Two-handed crossbow">Two-handed crossbow</a> <a href="/wiki/Weapons#Member_ranged_weapons" title="Weapons" class="mw-redirect">ranged weapon</a> that is part of <a href="/wiki/Karil_the_Tainted%27s_equipment" title="Karil the Tainted's equipment">Karil the Tainted's set</a> of <a href="/wiki/Barrows_equipment" title="Barrows equipment">barrows equipment</a>. To wield the crossbow players require a <a href="/wiki/Ranged" title="Ranged">Ranged</a> level of 70. It requires ammunition called <a href="/wiki/Bolt_rack" title="Bolt rack">bolt racks</a>. Both the Karil's crossbow and Karil's pistol crossbow are the only crossbows to use bolt racks.

4968 - <p><b>Torag's platebody</b> is <a href="/wiki/Armour#Melee_armour" title="Armour">melee armour</a> worn in the <a href="/wiki/Inventory#body_Slot" title="Inventory">body slot</a> that is part of <a href="/wiki/Torag_the_Corrupted%27s_equipment" title="Torag the Corrupted's equipment">Torag The Corrupted's set</a> of <a href="/wiki/Barrows_equipment" title="Barrows equipment">barrows equipment</a>. To wear Torag's platebody a player must have 70 <a href="/wiki/Defence" title="Defence">Defence</a>. Torag's platebody is also one of the strongest platebodies in RuneScape but it has the downside of degrading after 10 hours. When clicking "check" on the platebody it will show you its charges left. When it has fully degraded it turns to a broken torag's platebody.

10546 - <p><b>Healing vials</b> are used in <a href="/wiki/Barbarian_Assault" title="Barbarian Assault">Barbarian Assault</a> by the healer to heal teammates and holds 4 doses. It is made by getting an empty vial and taking it to the spring. Each dose heals the target player for a percentage of their maximum health which depends on the healer level.

10909 - <p><b>Mixture - step 1</b> is created by adding <a href="/wiki/Unicorn_horn_dust" title="Unicorn horn dust">unicorn horn dust</a> to <a href="/wiki/Super_restore_potion" title="Super restore potion" class="mw-redirect">Super restore potions</a>. <a href="/wiki/Clean_snake_weed" title="Clean snake weed">Clean snake weed</a> and <a href="/wiki/Nail_beast_nails" title="Nail beast nails">nail beast nails</a> can be added to make this potion into <a href="/wiki/Sanfew_serum" title="Sanfew serum">Sanfew serum</a>. After <a href="/wiki/Clean_snake_weed" title="Clean snake weed">snake weed</a> is added the potion becomes <a href="/wiki/Mixture_-_step_2" title="Mixture - step 2">Mixture - step 2</a>.

11500 - 0 coins
11501 - <div class="floatleft"><a href="http://vignette2.wikia.nocookie.net/runescape2/images/c/c6/Antidote%2B_mix_detail.png/revision/latest?cb=20140109005915" 	class="image image-thumbnail" 	 	 	><img src="data:image/gif;base64R0lGODlhAQABAIABAAAAAP///yH5BAEAAAEALAAAAAABAAEAQAICTAEAOw%3D%3D" 	 alt="Antidote+ mix detail" 	class="lzy lzyPlcHld " 	 	data-image-key="Antidote%2B_mix_detail.png" 	data-image-name="Antidote+ mix detail.png" 	 data-src="http://vignette2.wikia.nocookie.net/runescape2/images/c/c6/Antidote%2B_mix_detail.png/revision/latest/scale-to-width-down/50?cb=20140109005915" 	 width="50" 	 height="80" 	 	 	 onload="if(typeof ImgLzy=== #39;object #39;){ImgLzy.load(this)}" 	><noscript><img src="http://vignette2.wikia.nocookie.net/runescape2/images/c/c6/Antidote%2B_mix_detail.png/revision/latest/scale-to-width-down/50?cb=20140109005915" 	 alt="Antidote+ mix detail" 	class="" 	 	data-image-key="Antidote%2B_mix_detail.png" 	data-image-name="Antidote+ mix detail.png" 	 	 width="50" 	 height="80" 	 	 	 	></noscript></a></div>An <b>Antidote+ mix</b> is a <a href="/wiki/Barbarian_Potions#Barbarian_potions" title="Barbarian Potions" class="mw-redirect">Barbarian potion</a> that cures poison status and gives poison immunity for 9 minutes as well as healing 600 <a href="/wiki/Life_points" title="Life points">life points</a> per dose. It is made by using <a href="/wiki/Caviar" title="Caviar">Caviar</a> on a <a href="/wiki/Antipoison%2B_(2)" title="Antipoison+ (2)" class="mw-redirect">Antipoison+ (2)</a>. It requires a <a href="/wiki/Herblore" title="Herblore">Herblore</a> level of 74 to make and gives 52 experience. This mix can only be created after completing the Herblore part of <a href="/wiki/Barbarian_training" title="Barbarian training" class="mw-redirect">Barbarian training</a> with <a href="/wiki/Otto_Godblessed" title="Otto Godblessed">Otto Godblessed</a>. If the player drinks all doses or empties the potion it will become a regular empty <a href="/wiki/Vial" title="Vial">vial</a>.

11503 - <div class="floatleft"><a href="http://vignette2.wikia.nocookie.net/runescape2/images/c/c6/Antidote%2B_mix_detail.png/revision/latest?cb=20140109005915" 	class="image image-thumbnail" 	 	 	><img src="data:image/gif;base64R0lGODlhAQABAIABAAAAAP///yH5BAEAAAEALAAAAAABAAEAQAICTAEAOw%3D%3D" 	 alt="Antidote+ mix detail" 	class="lzy lzyPlcHld " 	 	data-image-key="Antidote%2B_mix_detail.png" 	data-image-name="Antidote+ mix detail.png" 	 data-src="http://vignette2.wikia.nocookie.net/runescape2/images/c/c6/Antidote%2B_mix_detail.png/revision/latest/scale-to-width-down/50?cb=20140109005915" 	 width="50" 	 height="80" 	 	 	 onload="if(typeof ImgLzy=== #39;object #39;){ImgLzy.load(this)}" 	><noscript><img src="http://vignette2.wikia.nocookie.net/runescape2/images/c/c6/Antidote%2B_mix_detail.png/revision/latest/scale-to-width-down/50?cb=20140109005915" 	 alt="Antidote+ mix detail" 	class="" 	 	data-image-key="Antidote%2B_mix_detail.png" 	data-image-name="Antidote+ mix detail.png" 	 	 width="50" 	 height="80" 	 	 	 	></noscript></a></div>An <b>Antidote+ mix</b> is a <a href="/wiki/Barbarian_Potions#Barbarian_potions" title="Barbarian Potions" class="mw-redirect">Barbarian potion</a> that cures poison status and gives poison immunity for 9 minutes as well as healing 600 <a href="/wiki/Life_points" title="Life points">life points</a> per dose. It is made by using <a href="/wiki/Caviar" title="Caviar">Caviar</a> on a <a href="/wiki/Antipoison%2B_(2)" title="Antipoison+ (2)" class="mw-redirect">Antipoison+ (2)</a>. It requires a <a href="/wiki/Herblore" title="Herblore">Herblore</a> level of 74 to make and gives 52 experience. This mix can only be created after completing the Herblore part of <a href="/wiki/Barbarian_training" title="Barbarian training" class="mw-redirect">Barbarian training</a> with <a href="/wiki/Otto_Godblessed" title="Otto Godblessed">Otto Godblessed</a>. If the player drinks all doses or empties the potion it will become a regular empty <a href="/wiki/Vial" title="Vial">vial</a>.

13160 - <p>The <b>Tome of xp 2nd ed</b> is given as a reward for completing the <a href="/wiki/Legacy_of_Seergaze" title="Legacy of Seergaze">Legacy of Seergaze</a> <a href="/wiki/Quest" title="Quest" class="mw-redirect">quest</a>. It gives the player 2500 <a href="/wiki/Experience" title="Experience">experience</a> points in any skill that's at least level 35 up to 3 times in total.
13161 - <p>The <b>Tome of xp 2nd ed</b> is given as a reward for completing the <a href="/wiki/Legacy_of_Seergaze" title="Legacy of Seergaze">Legacy of Seergaze</a> <a href="/wiki/Quest" title="Quest" class="mw-redirect">quest</a>. It gives the player 2500 <a href="/wiki/Experience" title="Experience">experience</a> points in any skill that's at least level 35 up to 3 times in total.
13162 - <p>The <b>Tome of xp 2nd ed</b> is given as a reward for completing the <a href="/wiki/Legacy_of_Seergaze" title="Legacy of Seergaze">Legacy of Seergaze</a> <a href="/wiki/Quest" title="Quest" class="mw-redirect">quest</a>. It gives the player 2500 <a href="/wiki/Experience" title="Experience">experience</a> points in any skill that's at least level 35 up to 3 times in total.

13677 - <p><b>Acrobat shirts</b> are obtained through <a href="/wiki/Balthazar_Beauregard%27s_Big_Top_Bonanza" title="Balthazar Beauregard's Big Top Bonanza">Balthazar Beauregard's Big Top Bonanza</a> which is a part of <a href="/wiki/Distractions_and_Diversions" title="Distractions and Diversions">Distractions and Diversions</a>. These are rewarded to players who earn between 501 and 1000 points in any of the circus performances.

13899 - <p><b>Vesta's longsword</b> is the fourth strongest longsword in the game beaten only by the <a href="/wiki/Chaotic_longsword" title="Chaotic longsword">chaotic longsword</a> <a href="/wiki/Drygore_longsword" title="Drygore longsword">drygore longsword</a> and the <a href="/wiki/Tetsu_katana" title="Tetsu katana">tetsu katana</a>. It is obtained by killing <a href="/wiki/Revenants" title="Revenants">Revenants</a> in the <a href="/wiki/Forinthry_Dungeon" title="Forinthry Dungeon">Forinthry Dungeon</a> or the <a href="/wiki/Chaos_Elemental" title="Chaos Elemental">Chaos Elemental</a> in very deep <a href="/wiki/Wilderness" title="Wilderness">Wilderness</a> and is considered the best drop possible from said foes. This piece of weaponry was released with the release of PvP worlds on <a href="/wiki/15_October" title="15 October">15 October</a> <a href="/wiki/2008" title="2008">2008</a>.

13901 - <p><b>Vesta's longsword</b> is the fourth strongest longsword in the game beaten only by the <a href="/wiki/Chaotic_longsword" title="Chaotic longsword">chaotic longsword</a> <a href="/wiki/Drygore_longsword" title="Drygore longsword">drygore longsword</a> and the <a href="/wiki/Tetsu_katana" title="Tetsu katana">tetsu katana</a>. 14094 - <div class="floatleft"><a href="http://vignette1.wikia.nocookie.net/runescape2/images/2/27/Sacred_clay_platebody_detail.png/revision/latest?cb=20111128031622" 	class="image image-thumbnail" 	 	 	><img src="http://vignette1.wikia.nocookie.net/runescape2/images/2/27/Sacred_clay_platebody_detail.png/revision/latest/scale-to-width-down/150?cb=20111128031622" 	 alt="Sacred clay platebody detail" 	class="" 	 	data-image-key="Sacred_clay_platebody_detail.png" 	data-image-name="Sacred clay platebody detail.png" 	 	 width="150" 	 height="168" 	 	 	 	></a></div>

14096 - <div class="floatleft"><a href="http://vignette4.wikia.nocookie.net/runescape2/images/6/61/Sacred_clay_helm_detail.png/revision/latest?cb=20110814222403" 	class="image image-thumbnail" 	 	 	><img src="http://vignette4.wikia.nocookie.net/runescape2/images/6/61/Sacred_clay_helm_detail.png/revision/latest/scale-to-width-down/100?cb=20110814222403" 	 alt="Sacred clay helm detail" 	class="" 	 	data-image-key="Sacred_clay_helm_detail.png" 	data-image-name="Sacred clay helm detail.png" 	 	 width="100" 	 height="114" 	 	 	 	></a></div>
14097 - <p>The <b>sacred clay scimitar</b> is a weapon obtained from the <a href="/wiki/Stealing_Creation" title="Stealing Creation">Stealing Creation</a> <a href="/wiki/Minigame" title="Minigame" class="mw-redirect">minigame</a> as a reward requiring 50 <a href="/wiki/Attack" title="Attack">attack</a> to wield. It can be bought from the <a href="/wiki/Rewards_mystic" title="Rewards mystic">Rewards mystic</a> for 26 reward points as a "morphic weapon" and can then be transformed into a melee ranged or magic weapon. Upon transforming it into a melee weapon it gives 24450 bonus experience in either <a href="/wiki/Attack" title="Attack">Attack</a> <a href="/wiki/Strength" title="Strength">Strength</a> or <a href="/wiki/Defence" title="Defence">Defence</a>. It does considerably more damage than a <a href="/wiki/Rune_scimitar" title="Rune scimitar">rune scimitar</a> and even more damage than a <a href="/wiki/Dragon_scimitar" title="Dragon scimitar">dragon scimitar</a> although it does not provide as much accuracy as the dragon scimitar.
14098 - <p>The <b>Volatile tool</b> is an item obtained by playing the <a href="/wiki/Stealing_Creation" title="Stealing Creation">Stealing Creation</a> <a href="/wiki/Minigame" title="Minigame" class="mw-redirect">minigame</a> and requires level 50 in the appropriate skill to use. When the tool is operated it will randomly transform into one of the following tools: <a href="/wiki/Volatile_clay_pickaxe" title="Volatile clay pickaxe">pickaxe</a> <a href="/wiki/Volatile_clay_hatchet" title="Volatile clay hatchet">hatchet</a> <a href="/wiki/Volatile_clay_harpoon" title="Volatile clay harpoon">harpoon</a> <a href="/wiki/Volatile_clay_butterfly_net" title="Volatile clay butterfly net">butterfly net</a> <a href="/wiki/Volatile_clay_hammer" title="Volatile clay hammer">hammer</a> <a href="/wiki/Volatile_Clay_Needle" title="Volatile Clay Needle" class="mw-redirect">needle</a> or a <a href="/wiki/Volatile_clay_fletching_knife" title="Volatile clay fletching knife">fletching knife</a>. Since <a href="/wiki/8_October" title="8 October">8 October</a> <a href="/wiki/2013" title="2013">2013</a> one may store 29340 <a href="/wiki/Bonus_experience" title="Bonus experience">bonus experience</a> by transforming the tool causing the player to earn double experience in that skill until all stored bonus experience is used up. All versions of the volatile tool can also be used for normal actions (such as a knife for <a href="/wiki/Fletching" title="Fletching">Fletching</a> or a hatchet for <a href="/wiki/Woodcutting" title="Woodcutting">Woodcutting</a>) but once the bonus experience is gained it is not necessary to carry the discharged tools around to benefit from it.

14102 - <div class="floatleft"><a href="http://vignette2.wikia.nocookie.net/runescape2/images/2/28/Volatile_clay_butterfly_net_detail.png/revision/latest?cb=20140926111154" 	class="image image-thumbnail" 	 	 	><img src="http://vignette2.wikia.nocookie.net/runescape2/images/2/28/Volatile_clay_butterfly_net_detail.png/revision/latest/scale-to-width-down/150?cb=20140926111154" 	 alt="Volatile clay butterfly net detail" 	class="" 	 	data-image-key="Volatile_clay_butterfly_net_detail.png" 	data-image-name="Volatile clay butterfly net detail.png" 	 	 width="150" 	 height="169" 	 	 	 	></a></div>
14103 - <p>The <b>volatile fletching knife</b> is created by operating the <a href="/wiki/Volatile_clay_tool" title="Volatile clay tool">volatile clay tool</a>. It is used in the <a href="/wiki/Fletching" title="Fletching">Fletching</a> skill and gives 29340 <a href="/wiki/Bonus_experience" title="Bonus experience">bonus experience</a>. It is obtained through the <a href="/wiki/Stealing_Creation" title="Stealing Creation">Stealing Creation</a> minigame and costs 20 Stealing Creation points to purchase. Once the bonus experience is gained it is not necessary to carry the discharged tools around to benefit from it. The tool will lose 10% of its potential bonus experience if you revert it. If you attempt to revert it when it is depleted it will be destroyed. 
14104 - <p>The <b>volatile clay hammer</b> is one of the possible tools that the <a href="/wiki/Volatile_Tool" title="Volatile Tool" class="mw-redirect">Volatile Tool</a> can transform into. The hammer gives a 29340 <a href="/wiki/Bonus_experience" title="Bonus experience">bonus experience</a> in the <a href="/wiki/Smithing" title="Smithing">smithing</a> or <a href="/wiki/Construction" title="Construction">construction</a> skill. Once the bonus experience is gained it is not necessary to carry the discharged tools around to benefit from it. The tool will lose 10% of its potential bonus experience if you revert it. If you attempt to revert it when it is depleted it will be destroyed. This item can be found on a members world in the <a href="/wiki/Stealing_Creation" title="Stealing Creation">Stealing Creation</a>  activity.
14105 - <p>A <b>volatile clay needle</b> is one of the possible tools that the <a href="/wiki/Volatile_Tool" title="Volatile Tool" class="mw-redirect">Volatile Tool</a> can transform into. The needle gives  29340 <a href="/wiki/Bonus_experience" title="Bonus experience">bonus experience</a> in the <a href="/wiki/Crafting" title="Crafting">Crafting</a> skill and it can be obtained by chance in the <a href="/wiki/Stealing_Creation" title="Stealing Creation">Stealing Creation</a> <a href="/wiki/Minigame" title="Minigame" class="mw-redirect">minigame</a> by purchasing the <a href="/wiki/Volatile_Tool" title="Volatile Tool" class="mw-redirect">Volatile Tool</a> for 20 stealing creation points and making it transform. Once the bonus experience is gained it is not necessary to carry the discharged tools around to benefit from it. The tool will lose 10% of its potential bonus experience if you revert it. If you attempt to revert it when it is depleted it will be destroyed.

14114 - <p>The <b>sacred clay robe top</b> is a reward from the <a href="/wiki/Stealing_Creation" title="Stealing Creation">Stealing Creation</a> minigame. It requires level 50 in both Magic and Defence to wear.
14115 - <p>The <b>sacred clay robe bottom</b> is a reward from the <a href="/wiki/Stealing_Creation" title="Stealing Creation">Stealing Creation</a> minigame. The sacred clay robe bottom gives 24450 bonus experience in the <a href="/wiki/Magic" title="Magic">Magic</a> skill. It may be recharged by spending 20 Stealing Creation points at the sacred clay reward mystic.
14116 - <div class="floatleft"><a href="http://vignette1.wikia.nocookie.net/runescape2/images/4/47/Sacred_clay_hat_chathead.png/revision/latest?cb=20120208223027" 	class="image image-thumbnail" 	 	 	><img src="http://vignette1.wikia.nocookie.net/runescape2/images/4/47/Sacred_clay_hat_chathead.png/revision/latest?cb=20120208223027" 	 alt="Sacred clay hat chathead" 	class="" 	 	data-image-key="Sacred_clay_hat_chathead.png" 	data-image-name="Sacred clay hat chathead.png" 	 	 width="119" 	 height="118" 	 	 	 	></a></div>A <b>Sacred clay hat</b> is an <a href="/wiki/Items" title="Items">item</a> that can be purchased for 24 points from the <a href="/wiki/Stealing_Creation" title="Stealing Creation">Stealing Creation</a> Rewards Shop. It is worn as a hat and requires 50 <a href="/wiki/Magic" title="Magic">Magic</a> and <a href="/wiki/Defence" title="Defence">Defence</a> to be able to wear it. It is bought in the <a href="/wiki/Morphic_head_armour" title="Morphic head armour">Morphic head armour</a> option while talking to the <a href="/wiki/Rewards_mystic" title="Rewards mystic">Rewards mystic</a>. Transforming the <a href="/wiki/Morphic_head_armour" title="Morphic head armour">Morphic head armour</a> into the hat will yield 24450 bonus experience in the <a href="/wiki/Magic" title="Magic">Magic</a> skill. It can be recharged at the <a href="/wiki/Stealing_Creation" title="Stealing Creation">Stealing Creation</a> rewards shop which costs 20 points. It has the exact same bonuses of a <a href="/wiki/Batwing_hood" title="Batwing hood">Batwing hood</a>.
14117 - <p>The <b>sacred clay staff</b> is a weapon obtained as a reward from <a href="/wiki/Stealing_Creation" title="Stealing Creation">Stealing Creation</a>. Most players do not use it since it does not provide infinite runes of any element unlike <a href="/wiki/Elemental_staves" title="Elemental staves">elemental staves</a>.
14118 - <p>The <b>Sacred clay body</b> is a piece of Ranged body armour bought in <a href="/wiki/Stealing_Creation" title="Stealing Creation">Stealing Creation</a> minigame which has stats identical to the <a href="/wiki/Blue_d%27hide_body" title="Blue d'hide body">Blue d'hide body</a>. This armour requires 50 defence and 50 range to wear. 
14119 - <p><b>Sacred clay chaps</b> is part of the ranger's set of <a href="/wiki/Sacred_clay_equipment" title="Sacred clay equipment">Sacred Clay armour</a>. They are bought from the rewards mystic for 28 Stealing creation points. It is the leg piece and requires level 50 <a href="/wiki/Defence" title="Defence">Defence</a> and <a href="/wiki/Ranged" title="Ranged">Ranged</a> to wear. They give 24450 bonus experience in the <a href="/wiki/Ranged" title="Ranged">Ranged</a> skill. They may be recharged for 20 reward points.
14120 - <div class="floatleft"><a href="http://vignette2.wikia.nocookie.net/runescape2/images/3/3e/Sacred_clay_coif_detail.png/revision/latest?cb=20110814225028" 	class="image image-thumbnail" 	 title="Sacred clay coif detailed" 	 	><img src="http://vignette2.wikia.nocookie.net/runescape2/images/3/3e/Sacred_clay_coif_detail.png/revision/latest/scale-to-width-down/80?cb=20110814225028" 	 alt="Sacred clay coif detail" 	class="" 	 	data-image-key="Sacred_clay_coif_detail.png" 	data-image-name="Sacred clay coif detail.png" 	 	 width="80" 	 height="143" 	 	 	 	></a></div>
14121 - <p>The <b>Sacred clay bow</b> is a weapon obtained as a reward from <a href="/wiki/Stealing_Creation" title="Stealing Creation">Stealing Creation</a>. It offers the same bonuses and speed as a <a href="/wiki/Magic_shortbow" title="Magic shortbow">magic shortbow</a> and just like the magic shortbow requires 50 <a href="/wiki/Ranged" title="Ranged">Ranged</a> to wield.
